.TH SP-AUDIT-LEGIBILITY 1 "Spherepop Tools" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sp-audit-legibility \- local text heuristic for compressibility and proceduralization
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sp-audit-legibility
.RB [ \-f " file" ]
.RB [ \-t " threshold" ]
.RB [ \-o " out.txt" ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
sp-audit-legibility reads text from a file or standard input and emits a report
estimating whether the text has become highly compressible and strongly
procedural (a proxy for "executable without context").
.PP
This tool is local-only and non-operational: it does not access networks or
external systems.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-f " file"
Input file. If omitted, reads from standard input.
.TP
.BI \-t " threshold"
Legibility risk threshold (default: 55).
.TP
.BI \-o " file"
Output report file (default: ./legibility.txt).
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, non-zero on error.
.SH SEE ALSO
sp-sim-observer(1)

